	<tr>
		<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
	
			<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
			Ok, finally got my J Boots this weekend so I thought I'd add some info on the Hasten Bootstrutter &quot;problem&quot;. <BR>
Hasten, it seems, will not appear as long as the monk Brother Zephyl(sp?) is around. This guy is a lvl 50 monk who hits for 350 a pop and runs faster than SoW. The -problem- is that he tends to get stuck on the &quot;sticky rock&quot; near the scarab totem. This prevents him from despawning, and so Hasten never shows. After several different people tried to get GMs to come kill the bugger, one finally came and made him suicide. Then the monk shows AGAIN, only this time he was wearing a brown robe (go figure, but it was the same NPC). Anyways, long story short, the GM suicided that one too, and about 5 minutes later Hasten is spotted finally.<BR>
A word to the wise. Make sure you have SoW on, and as good of a strength buff as you can acquire. Hasten is a fast bugger, and if you dont have SoW and str on, you will be moving slower than a Giant Scarab in Halas with 3250 gold in your pockets. Also, once you get to Hasten, you can just give him the items (Ring, Rapier, and gold) No need to ask about all the quest items (I didnt and it worked fine). <BR>
Last note, this is a long and frustrating quest, and well worth it in the end =) It's nice to see Verant making challenging quests that actually have a decent reward at the end.<BR>
<BR>
Wayfarer Jones<BR>
42nd lvl Magician (at the time of getting the boots)<BR>
Bristlebane<BR>
 
			</font>
	
